    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>This collection contains 21 letters, arranged in nine folders by year, mostly written by James C. Chowning to his mother and sisters, during the Civil War and afterwards. They describe his training with the Tennessee Volunteers in the Confederate
        Army, and military operations of those troops. These letters provide a somewhat detailed description of training in the camps, of rumors among the troops, and his opinion of political events. A few letters were written from admirers to his sisters.
        Most of the letters are handwritten, some with a typescript.</p>
    </scopecontent>
